  "text": "Another such result, and that was our original motivation to introduce the formalism of preclones, is a nice algebraic characterization of F O[<]-definable tree languages (and a number of extensions of F O[<], such as the introduction of additional, modular quantifiers), briefly discussed in Section 5.2.4. Let us say immediately that we do not know yet whether this characterization can be turned into a decision algorithm! In order to keep this paper within a reasonable number of pages, this characterization will be the subject of another paper by the same authors [CITATION_1] . The main results of this upcoming paper can be found, along with an outline of the present paper, in [CITATION_2] .",
